      • createSet

        protected Set<O> createSet(int initialSize)
        Creates a Set in which this collection will store objects.

        By default, this creates a set via: Collections.newSetFromMap(new ConcurrentHashMap<O, Boolean>(initialSize))

        Applications could optionally extend this class and override this method to return an alternative implementation.

        Parameters:
        initialSize - The initial size for the set
        Returns:
        A new instance of the Set

      • addIndex

        public void addIndex(Index<O> index)
        Adds the given index to the collection.

        Subsequently queries passed to the QueryEngine.retrieve(com.googlecode.cqengine.query.Query) methods will use these indexes if suitable for the particular queries, to speed up retrievals.
